content.description:
Thin Slice climbs a thin, sharp crack 6' left of Classic Crack.  The crack turns to shit and the rest of the climbing is done on blocks with intermittent gear till you get to the anchor of Classic Crack. 

  This climb is included for historical purposes only. It collapsed during the spring of 2012.
content.protection: Thin Slice is protected with gear to 3" and a 2 bolt chain anchor.

content.description: Super Clean starts 12' right of the main dihedral at the left end of the crag.  Climb on bolts up easy slab to an higher crux near the anchor.
content.protection: Super Clean is protected by 8 bolts and a 2 bolt chain anchor.

content.description: The Puzzler climbs a line of seven bolts up the right side of the crag.  The first half of this route is shared with Arch of Dimes before moving left on the upper face the merging back together at the anchor.  Due to the bottom of the climb falling down some aspects of this route may have changed so be careful.
content.protection: Puzzler is protected by 7 bolts and a 3 bolt anchor.

content.description: Left Face Crack starts on loose, crumbling rock and climbs to a sharp crack that will take small gear.  Once at the top of the steeper section follow two bolts to the anchor.
content.protection: Left Face Crack is protected by small gear, 2 bolts and a 2 bolt chain anchor.

content.description: This routes replaces the fallen first pitch of Classic Crack.  Provides an approach pitch to Classic Crack (aka I Love B) and Arch Crack
content.location: Obvious bolted lines, trends left to right then back left again.

climbs.name: Frigid Rigid
climbs.fa: Kelsey Gray, Kyle Arzt, Mike Allison '08

content.description: Frigid Rigid climbs the face on the right side of the Classic Crack anchor.  Make some tricky clips on the steep face then traverse left on a chossy ledge to the anchor.
content.protection: Frigid Rigid is protected by 4 bolts and a 2 bolt chain anchor.

content.description:
1st Pitch (5.8) The first pitch climbs through a few ledges and cracks.  The crux on the lower section is after gaining the first block pulling up onto the second ledge. 

  2nd Pitch (5.11) On the second ledge you can continue up two variants of 5.11 climbing or traverse left toward the anchor to access Classic Crack, Arch Crack & Frigid Rigid.
content.protection: Gear to 3"     Fixed Pro (6/14/17) there is a old hex with blue cord on the first ledge.  Second ledge there is an old Leeper hanger with some tat hanging off please don't clip this.

content.description: Face Crack starts on loose blockie climbing into a corner with an under cling.  From here get on to the slab and finish at the anchor.
content.protection: Face Crak is protected by 4 bolts and a 2 bolt chain anchor.

content.description: Ditchweed starts 30' right of Classic Crack and climbs a line of old bolts into a small corner.  Once over the top scramble right to the anchor of Classic Crack.
content.protection: Ditchweed is protected by 8 bolts and a 2 bolt chain anchor.

content.description: Deranged Spider climbs up the face on the first five bolts of Super Clean.  It then follows bolts out left to and up the arete and on to the anchor.  Use a long runner or skip the fifth bolt to cut down on rope drag.
content.protection: Deranged Spider is protected by 10 bolts and a 2 bolt chain anchor.

content.description: Cruiser is a newer sport route located on the far left  arete.  It is the first climb you will encounter at the north end of the crag.  Climb up broken rock to an anchor shared with Deranged Spider.
content.protection: Cruiser is protected by 7 bolts and a 2 bolt anchor.

climbs.name: Cosmic Connection
climbs.fa: Steve Garvey, Eddie Phay, Dino Banco '96

content.description: Cosmic Connection starts at the anchor of Super Clean.  Cut right down low then climb up a corner that will get steeper and steeper.  Pull the lip and climb to an anchor at the top of the cliff.
content.protection: Cosmic Connetion is protected with 5 bolts, 1 piton and a 2 bolt anchor.

content.description:
A fun crack that protects well and is a great after work style multipitch.  A little loose rock but not awful for the arm.  Follow an open book to a large ledge.  Belay from the 2 bolt here and continue to the top via the wide crack system passing over some very loose rock at top.  3 bolt anchor for the rappel.   

Edit

I've been told that Classic Crack has collapsed and is no more.  Sad day indeed.
content.protection: #.75-#3 cams.  I brought nuts but didn't place them.  Go heavy on the bigger pieces.  2 bolt anchor on top of the first pitch and 3 bolt anchor at the very top.
content.location: Start almost dead center in the wall following the large crack to the middle ledge.  Belay from here to get to the top anchors following the large crack system.

content.description: Arch of Dimes climbs a line of seven bolts up the right side of the crag.  The first half of this route is shared with Puzzler before moving right on the upper face the merging back together at the anchor.  Due to the bottom of the climb falling down some aspects of this route may have changed so be careful.
content.protection: Arch of Dimes is protected by 9 bolts and a 3 bolt anchor.

content.description: Climb up the first pitch of Classic Crack or anything that gets you up to the large ledge system with the two bolt anchor.  From the anchor the climb is left about 15 feet and starts under a small roof.  Climb under this roof pulling big fun holds until you exit out right and then head over to the jug haul flake system.  Climb up this until you get back onto Classic Crack and take it to the 3 bolt anchor up top.
content.protection: Standard rack to a #3.  Bring slings for the placements under the roof.
content.location: In the middle of the wall is the Classic Crack first pitch which will take you to a ledge with a 2 bolted anchor with comically long chains.  From here look left to find Arch Cracks.

content.description: A large amphitheater that is 2.5 miles past the Weigh Station when coming from Anchorage.  Park at Boy Scout rock parking lot or simply turn around and pull your vehicle over to the side of the road far enough to be out of traffic.  If you climb past 9PM there tends to be very little traffic, and hell you live in AK take advantage of the long days!  Otherwise expect to never hear your partner due to the ocean and highway.  The rock quality is generally pretty bad but isn't terrible for Seward Highway.  Watch yourself in the spring when the rock has been frost wedged out and can lead to holds that weren't previously loose falling out.  Protect often.  One of the few places that you can "multi-pitch" on the highway with a few routes being short two pitchers.
